* Static Keyword

1. Static Variables: Belong to the class, not individual instances.
Shared among all objects of the class.

➡️ agr static variable bnaya h to usse esa likhna padega

static int variableName;
static{
  variableName = 0;
}

➡️ static variable ko class ka naam lga ke access kiya jata h
   className.staticVariable = ....;

2. Static Methods: Can be called without creating an object of the class.
Can only directly access static variables and other static methods.

3. No Access to Non-static Members: Static methods and blocks cannot directly access
   non-static members (variables and methods) of the class.
